cpp-clibars
------------------------------------------
CLIBars is a easy to use and customizable library to show elegant ascii
progress bars on the terminal.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libclibars-devel-1.0.0-1bl1
  libclibars0-1.0.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/tbhaxor/cpp-clibars

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/tbhaxor/cpp-clibars/archive/v1.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cpp-clibars-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cpp-clibars-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cpp-clibars-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cpp-clibars-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libclibars0-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libclibars-devel-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(cpp-clibars)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/cpp-clibars.README
  /usr/share/doc/cpp-clibars/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/cpp-clibars/README.md

(libclibars0)
  /usr/bin/cygclibars-0.dll

(libclibars-devel)
  /usr/include/clibars.hpp
  /usr/lib/libclibars.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/clibars.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

